****** Idea from Misce in room 554 on Tue Aug 14 03:17:38 2001:
Subject: [Idea] completing the financial loop
It seems that as shops stock up the market for loot of anything low level comes to a halt and it becomes increasingly difficult to sell the wares.  Quite a lo t of rewards for killing mobs simply arent worth it because the shops have too many of that. It may be a good idea to have mobs purchasing cheap, level relative armor/weapons from stores to keep the cycle moving.  This would also serve to  balance out the mob/player power problems brought on by elimination of rent limits. 
