****** Idea from Delanea in room 238 on Tue Feb 12 13:01:27 2002:
Subject: [Idea] Smything fun
Hey. Laren has a ton of fun with smythe, but she runs into weird scenarios that don't make sense. What mostly doesn't make sense is that you wield everything! Like, you're going to USE it. :) What would make more sense is to have some special way of holding, specifically for smything.  Obviously, smythers don't always have the ability to wield everything they should be able to smythe. But that doesn't mean they should not be able to smythe it anyways. :) Such as, say, long silver daggers.  I can't hold them, so I can't smythe them. But actual blacksmith types don't have such restrictions because they don't wield the weapons to USE them.  They're just fixing them.   Is there any way to change the way we smythe so we have a special method of holding things specifically for smything?  Obviously, we can't attack using the weapons we're holding to smythe.  It just won't work, just like if a smyther tries to attack holding the weapon she's smything!  Also, it seems there should be some way to smythe heavy things, like suits. If Piggot can do it, why can''t we?  Because we're limited by the ability to use the regular hold.  Maybe it would require a special tool or something to assist us, but that's ok... Smythers use more tools than a hammer. :)  I just very much enjoy fixing people's equipment and weapons, and I've spent a lot of time honing smythe (one of the hardest things to hone), and am disappointed when I can get everything but the suit smythed up to brand new again.  :)  Same with, say, the silver dagger and other things I'm forbidden to hold.  Monogrammed items, for instance.  And, the impressive deikhan weapons.   I don't wish, in any way, to find a back door to being able to WIELD these weapons, but want to fix them. :) Wonder if there's some other way to do this?  It seems logical enough.:)  Thanks! Laren 
